  <div class="single-column content">
    <p>In our theory articles, we focus on the ecological-dynamics framework, as well as non-linear pedagogy and the constraints-led approach. We want to make these theories, methods and concepts more accessible.</p>
    <p>These theories challenge some traditional assumptions about skill acquisition and motor learning. They also might help you understand better why you do what you do.</p>
    <p>Our how-to articles offer a more practical approach, and are meant to develop sound, evidence-based coaching principles, while also aiming to spark creative and novel solutions.</p>
    <p>Finally, we also examine case studies from different sport, physical activities or coaching methods, from the perspective of ecological-dynamics. What can we learn from these cases? Could they be improved?</p>
  </div>

